    • Method Detail

      • getSession

        SessionValue<Req,Res> getSession(SessionId id)
        Returns the SessionValue based on the SessionId provided. If multiple values exists for the same key, only the head SessionValue element will be retrieved. This is somehow similar to peek() in Queue based implementations. The ordering is guaranteed by the SessionValue index.
        Parameters:
        id - The SessionId instance to be used as the lookup key.
        Returns:
        A SessionValue or NULL if no session found for the specified id

      • getSession

        SessionValue<Req,Res> getSession(AbstractMessage message)
        Get session based on the AbstractMessage instance
        Parameters:
        message - The AbstractMessage instance to use for the lookup reference
        Returns:
        A SessionValue instance if found. Null if a session does not exists for the specified AbstractMessage

      • getId

        SessionId getId(AbstractMessage message)
        Returns the session id from the registry.
        Parameters:
        message - An instance of AbstractMessage to use as a reference for the SessionId lookup.
        Returns:
        The SessionId instance retrieved from the registry. Null if no SessionId has been found in the registry for the message.

      • register

        SessionId register(RequestDetails<Req,Res> requestDetails)
        Registers the request to the session registry. This should be used once a request has been delivered via the underlying transport. If the same request type already exists in the registry, it will not replace the existing, rather it will be placed within the same collection under the same SessionId.
        Parameters:
        requestDetails - A RequestDetails instance containing the details of the request.
        Returns:
        A SessionId if the request has been successfully registered.

      • unregister

        boolean unregister(SessionId id)
        Removes the associated session from the registry (if available) using a SessionId instance. This will try to retrieve the existing SessionValue from the registry using the id provided. If multiple sessions exists for this id, then only the top SessionValue will be removed.
        Parameters:
        id - The SessionId instance to be used as the lookup reference for the session.
        Returns:
        true if the operation has been successful.

      • unregister

        boolean unregister(SessionValue value)
        Removes the associated session from the registry (if available) using the SessionValue provided.
        Parameters:
        value - The SessionValue instance to be used as the lookup reference for the session.
        Returns:
        true if the operation has been successful.

      • isRegistered

        boolean isRegistered(AbstractMessage message)
        This lookups the session registry map and indicates whether or not the message is in the registry or not
        Parameters:
        message - An instance of AbstractMessage to be used as the lookup reference in the registry.
        Returns:
        true if the specified message is registered in the session registry otherwise false.
